HEADWORD: Wildering
<hw>Wild"er*ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A plant growing in a state of nature; especially, one which has run
wild, or escaped from cultivation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

